      What is Software Engineering? - Definition from Techopedia

      https://www.techopedia.com/definition/13296/software-engineering

      Software engineering is a branch of computer science12 and a systematic engineering approach234 that deals with the design, development, testing, maintenance, and evaluation2345 of complex computer software13 or software applications24 that satisfy user needs45. A software engineer is a person who applies engineering principles and programming languages245 to build software solutions25. The term programmer may or may not imply engineering skills3.

      What Does Software Engineering Mean? Software engineering is the process of analyzing user needs and designing, constructing, and testing end-user applications that will satisfy these needs through the use of software programming languages. It is the application of engineering principles to software development.
